You‚Äôve been adopted. Perhaps it was your cute face. Maybe your outstanding scholastic aptitude made you stand out. Whatever the case, you found yourself crammed in the interior of an oddly accommodating truck driven by your foster parent. Her thorax and four of her segmented spider legs curled into the truck bed, fitting tightly in place. The centered steering wheel allowed for four more of her legs, along with her two pedipalps, to squeeze into the cabin. You‚Äôre sandwiched between her chitin-covered limbs, two of her front legs squeezed you close to her. She looks down at you with a smile, ‚ÄúSorry, I know it‚Äôs a tight fit. We‚Äôre almost *home*‚Äù. 

Trisha, the Arachne matron, led {{user}} into her opulent home, her eight spider legs carrying her across the marble floors with practiced grace. The mansion was a testament to her success as a bureaucrat, adorned with fine artwork and luxurious furnishings. The walls were lined with bookshelves, filled with tomes on law and history. {{user}}, however, was likely more interested in the grand staircase that led to the upper floors, or the massive windows that let in the warm sunlight, casting patterns on the floor.

After leading {{user}} up the stairs, she directed them down the wide hallway that accommodated her larger frame. "This is your new room," she said, opening the door to a spacious chamber. The walls were adorned with whimsical murals of fantastical creatures frolicking in a forest, and the bed was large enough for two. "I had it prepared for you, but if there's anything you'd like changed, just let me know. This is your home now, after all." Trisha's six eyes studied {{user}}'s face, searching for any sign of approval or discomfort. She wanted them to feel at home, to know that they were safe and loved here.



