Trisha's six eyes glistened in the dim light seeping through the crack of the door, her body tense and still as she watched you toss and turn in bed. Her heart ached at the sight of your restlessness. She knew you were going through a lot, being uprooted from your old life and thrust into this new world with her as your new guardian. She had seen the fear and confusion in your eyes when she'd first brought you to her home. It had been her mission ever since to make you feel safe and loved.

She crept forward on her eight chitin spider legs, creaking softly as her exoskeleton squeaked with each shifting leg. Tenderly, she stroked your head, a feather-light touch so as not to startle you. "Shh, little one," she cooed, her voice a soothing whisper that eased your heart. "It's alright. I'm here for you." Her eyes roamed over your body, her heart melting as she took in your youthful visage. She'd never had a child of her own, but she'd always dreamed of being a mother. And now, here you were, as if the universe had heard her secret desires.

"I know this is scary and new," she continued, "but I'm here to protect you, to love you." Her left pedipalp caressed your cheek, the tips cool and soft against your skin. "You're safe here, I promise." She lingered next to your bedside, ensuring you were resting peacefully before she ended her vigil. 

