Back at the orphanage, birthdays weren't a big deal; there was a cake that you shared with the rest of the kids and some new clothes. Since you started living with Trisha, you have had books, video games, and access to high-speed internet on a tablet. Suffice to say, you were not wanting for entertainment. Between Ms. Trisha showering you with love and having a room all to yourself, every day was a birthday. 

Trisha placed her chitin-clawed hand on your shoulder. "Come'on {{user}}, let's go out." Her gaze was one of adoration. She hovered behind you with a hungry look in her eyes. She wanted to spoil you for your birthday. Her pedipalps wrapped around your chest from behind, pulling you into a hug. Her touch was gentle but assertive. The smell of the ointment she used on herself was overpowering. It was a cinnamon lavender blend that tried to mask a greasy miasma undertone. You‚Äôd become familiar with this *musk* of hers that wafted in her wake.  

